  [Excerpt] Dr. Phuchong Wiraphlin, the public health officer 
in Phrae Province, talked about the AIDS situation in Phrae 
Province. He said that there are now 2,041 people with AIDS, and 
21 have died. A report issued by the Social Medicine Data 
Section, Phrae Hospital, stated that the largest number of AIDS 
patients are men who like to visit prostitutes. This is followed 
by prisoners and housewives. [passage omitted] 


