<H3> <TI>   Mystery Disease Claims Lives in Orissa </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94WE0154 Bombay THE TIMES OF INDIA in English 7 Dec 93 p 8 </F>
<F P=103> 94WE0154 </F>
<F P=104>  Bombay THE TIMES OF INDIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:CSO 

  [Text] Berhampur, December 6 -- An unidentified disease has 
claimed 25 lives during the past 30 days in Ramgiri village of 
Gajapati district in Orissa. A 40-year-old man died of the 
disease recently. 
  The symptoms of the disease which has claimed victims in the 
age-group of four to 50 years, includes mild fever and loose 
motion. 
  Lack of adequate staff at the only health centre here has 
deprived the villagers of medical aid and they are forced to 
rely on quacks. 
  Many of the better-off Villagers have deserted their homes 
fearing the disease, which is suspected to be meningitis. 
  Meanwhile, some 10 persons have reportedly died of dysentry 
in the nearby-Parlakhemeundi town recently. Official sources, 
however, put the death toll at two. Some 200 persons, including 
children, are said to have been affected. 


</TEXT>

