<H3> <TI>   Foreign Workers Carrying Malaria Virus in Pahang </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2802125594 Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia in English 0800 
GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2802125594 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Some foreign workers have been found to be carriers 
of malaria. Pahang state director of medical and health 
services, Dr. R. Mahadevan, however, said it is difficult to 
control them, as they seldom stayed in one place for long. 
  Dr. Mahadevan said another source of malaria was the Orang 
Asli [aborigines] in the interior areas. They, too, move from 
place to place. 
  Pahang has the second highest rate of malaria cases after 
Sabah. 

</TEXT>

